.SH NAME
Touch.radiusX \- Touch: radiusX property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]radiusX\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]Touch\f[R] interface returns the X radius of the ellipse that most
closely circumscribes the area of contact with the touch surface.
The value is in CSS pixels of the same scale as
\f[CR]Touch.screenX\f[R].
.PP
This value, in combination with \f[CR]Touch.radiusY\f[R] and
\f[CR]Touch.rotationAngle\f[R] constructs an ellipse that approximates
the size and shape of the area of contact between the user and the
screen.
This may be a relatively large ellipse representing the contact between
a fingertip and the screen or a small area representing the tip of a
stylus, for example.
.SH VALUE
A number.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example illustrates using the \f[CR]Touch\f[R] interface\(cqs
\f[CR]Touch.radiusX\f[R], \f[CR]Touch.radiusX\f[R] and
\f[CR]Touch.rotationAngle\f[R] properties.
The \f[CR]Touch.radiusX\f[R] property is the radius of the ellipse which
most closely circumscribes the touching area (e.g., finger, stylus)
along the axis \f[B]indicated\f[R] by the touch point\(cqs
\f[CR]Touch.rotationAngle\f[R].
Likewise, the \f[CR]Touch.radiusY\f[R] property is the radius of the
ellipse which most closely circumscribes the touching area (e.g.,
finger, stylus) along the axis \f[B]perpendicular\f[R] to that indicated
by \f[CR]Touch.rotationAngle\f[R].
The \f[CR]Touch.rotationAngle\f[R] is the angle (in degrees) that the
ellipse described by \f[CR]radiusX\f[R] and \f[CR]radiusY\f[R] is
rotated clockwise about its center.
.PP
The following simple code snippet, registers a single handler for the
\f[CR]touchstart\f[R], \f[CR]touchmove\f[R] and \f[CR]touchend\f[R]
events.
When the \f[CR]src\f[R] element is touched, the element\(cqs width and
height will be calculate based on the touch point\(cqs
\f[CR]radiusX\f[R] and \f[CR]radiusY\f[R] values and the element will
then be rotated using the touch point\(cqs \f[CR]rotationAngle\f[R].
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R] id=\(dqsrc\(dq>\&...</\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
